{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1774367603,"nonce":"l1nGj3gbaoRjt7LMeZYRcRn2lwM=","message":"## Run 4: Complete Phase 1+2 results + APT implementation\n\n### All conditions tested\n\n| Condition | nn_output | Loss | Ep err | Peak speed | SISU 0→1 velocity |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| running_cost (standard) | 1e-5 | 32→3 | 0.007 | 3.33 | -0.3% |\n| CVaR 10% | 1e-5 | 32→17 | 0.109 | 3.18 | -0.9% |\n| nn_output 1e-4 (high) | 1e-4 | 32→714 | 0.780 | 2.63 | +4.1% (diverged) |\n| nn_output 1e-6 (low) | 1e-6 | 32→5.4 | 0.070 | 3.91 | -0.7% |\n| softmin | 1e-5 | DIVERGED | - | - | - |\n| default | 1e-5 | DIVERGED | - | - | - |\n| combined | 1e-5 | 11→5 | 0.152 | 2.06 | - |\n\n### Key finding (decoupled SISU test)\n\nWith fixed perturbation scale=0.5, varying only SISU input:\n- Endpoint error improves ~11% at moderate SISU (accuracy modulation)\n- Peak velocity is flat (-0.3%) — no velocity modulation\n- The network learns to use SISU for gain changes (LQG-like) but NOT trajectory changes (H∞-like)\n\n### APT implementation\n\nImplemented `pre_step_fn` hook on TaskTrainer. APT does 3 inner gradient ascent steps on perturbation forces per training step (Madry-style adversarial training). Smoke test passed. Running 2000-batch local CPU test (~3h). TPU timing test pending.\n\n### Figures\n\nAll available at results/part2_5/figures/:\n- fig_peak_velocity_by_sisu.html\n- fig_endpoint_error_by_sisu.html\n- fig_lateral_deviation_by_sisu.html\n- fig_loss_curves.html\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","files":null}]}